title: More Democrats warn Biden about how Israel is conducting response
description: Administration officials say that they are holding Israel accountable and that they share some of the same concerns that their fellow Democrats have raised.

title: Israel pounds Gaza from air and land; Biden presses for more aid
description: Communications in the besieged enclave, cut by Israel on Friday, where restored at the Biden administration’s urging, a senior U.S. official said.

title: Early stages of Israeli ground assault in Gaza shrouded in secrecy
description: Israeli officials have released little information about the ground assault underway in Gaza. But a general outline of the operation is emerging.

title: Israel’s Gaza offensive stirs a wave of global protest
description: As a terrifying silence fell over Gaza amid a near complete communications blackout, protesters around the world made noise to call for a cease-fire.

title: Latino voices on family, sports, legacy, music, tradition and language
description: Several Washington Post staffers determined to highlight the richness of their Latino culture decided to share their personal experiences through short essays.

title: Israel-Gaza live updates: Internet partially restored in Gaza; ‘second stage’ of war underway, Netanyahu says
description: As Israeli forces push into Gaza, the country’s officials would not definitely say whether the anticipated major ground incursion had begun.

title: Lebanon’s Hezbollah weighs dueling appeals: ease attacks or escalate
description: In struggling Lebanon, there is wide support for Gaza but also fear that the war could spread.

title: New danger for Ukraine: Taking Israel’s side in war against Hamas and Gaza
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky came out fast and strong in support of Israel but that has imperiled relations with Arab and Muslim nations.
